Eunic - A Bash script to Manage Unicorn

Setup and Install:
=======
You git cloned it, right? Do it now.

1. In the source directory where you downloaded this repo:

    cp eunic /usr/local/bin
    chmod +x /usr/local/bin/eunic

2. To install eunic:

   eunic -i /path/to/your/app

Command Usage:
==============

Restart:
    eunic -R production

Start:
    eunic -S production

Stop:
    eunic -s production

There is the USR reload thing in here but f'd if I can get USR to work. I should try again.

